stanford encyclopedia of philosophy http plato stanford edu page 1 for immediate release contact uri nodelman stanford encyclopedia of philosophy editors plato stanford edu 650 723 0488 stanford encyclopedia of philosophy wins best content in the charleston advisor reader's choice awards stanford california november 2005 the stanford encyclopedia of philosophy sep received the best content award from the charleston advisor in its fifth annual reader's choice awards the journal rated electronic services and databases for libraries the charles ton advisor described the sep as a project of superior quality within its discipline and con sidered the sep to be exemplary in pulling together many of the best experts in the field as contributors the award was announced in the october issue v 5 no 2 of the charleston advisor see http www charlestonco com features cfm id 188&type me john perry henry waldgrave stuart professor of philosophy at stanford university and faculty advisor to the sep said the stanford encyclopedia of philosophy has become the premier portal to philosophy on the world wide web by offering authoritative and in depth entries on the most important issues in contemporary philosophy it has become an invaluable learning and research tool for students and scholars alike edward zalta principal editor for the sep notes we are very pleased to receive this award the charleston advisor recognizes the value of a peer reviewed online resource for philoso phy the stanford encyclopedia of philosophy's contributing authors and editors some of the world's top philosophy scholars constantly amaze me by their commitment of time and energy their efforts make philosophical scholarship broadly available and accessible to everyone margaret landesman head of the collections department at the university of utah endorses the sep as an idea which validates our ideals of both scholarship and librarianship in bringing to everyone whether or not they can afford to pay a high quality tool of permanent value the sep http plato stanford edu is a pioneer in providing open access to a comprehensive online philosophy reference work that is authoritative peer reviewed and continually updated as many as 600000 times a week entries are retrieved from the sep's main server three mirror sites around the world receive an additional 35000 entry retrievals this many hits strongly suggests that the sep serves not only the community of professional philosophers but also is widely used by the public at large the sep's comprehensive archival system makes it easy for both students and scholars to cite any sep entry in their works librarians philosophers and other supporters have joined forces to ensure that the sep a sparc partner remains free widely accessible and generally available to all the national endowment for the humanities has supported the sep with a $500000 matching grant that earns a $1 match from the neh for every $3 contributed from libraries and affiliated institutions to learn more about how you can help please email fundraising plato stanford edu stanford encyclopedia of philosophy http plato stanford edu
